job.title: UP TET Online Form 2021– Apply Online for Uttar Pradesh Teacher Eligibility Test
job.body:
Total Vacancies: Not disclosed

Name of the post:

  • Teachers for Classes I-V (Primary Level), Classes VI-VIII (Upper Primary Level). 

Description:

The Uttar Pradesh Basic Education Board issued various vacancies for the posts of Classes I-V (Primary Level), Classes VI-VIII (Upper Primary Level). The online application for the posts of Classes I-V (Primary Level), Classes VI-VIII (Upper Primary Level) under Uttar Pradesh Basic Education Board shall start from 18-05-2021. The eligible candidates can apply for the online application before 01-06-2021. For further detailed information regarding educational qualifications, age limit, selection procedure, for Classes I-V (Primary Level), Classes VI-VIII (Upper Primary Level) mentioned below. For more such updates do visit theprograd.com .The ProGrad jobs.

 

Mode of application & application fee:

The interested candidates after filling the application form, it is required to pay the application fee to complete the form submission process:

  • Mode of application: Online

For Single Paper I or II: 

  • The application fee for the General/ OBC is INR 600/-
  • The application fee for SC/ ST is INR 400/-
  • The application fee for PwD is INR 100/-

For Both Papers:

  • The application fee for the General/ OBC is INR 1200/-
  • The application fee for SC/ ST is INR 800/-
  • The application fee for PwD is INR 200/-

For more details, you can refer to the notification. The link is given at the bottom.

Important dates:

  • The Starting date to apply online is 18-05-2021
  • The Last date to apply online is 01-06-2021
  • Last Date to Submit Registration Fee: 02-06-2021
  • Last Date to Submit Completed Registration/ Print Application Form: 03-06-2021
  • Date for Uploading of Admit Card on Website: 14-07-2021
  • Date for Exam (Paper I & II): 25-07-2021

Educational qualification required:

Candidates who are interested in Classes I-V (Primary Level), Classes VI-VIII (Upper Primary Level) should have the following qualification from a recognized University/boards :

Primary Level:

  • Passed 10+2 (Intermediate) Exam with 50% Marks and 4 Year B.LEd Degree OR
  • Bachelor Degree in Any Stream with B.Ed Degree OR
  • Diploma in Teacher From Aligarh Muslim University AMU, Aligarh OR
  • Moaalizm E Urdu Exam Passed OR
  • D.Ed Special Exam Passed
  • 2 Year BTC Or Special BTC Exam Passed

Junior Level: 

  • Bachelor Degree/ Master Degree with 50% Marks with B.Ed / B.Ed Special Exam Passed OR
  • Bachelor Degree/ Master Degree with BTC Training 2 Year Exam Passed OR
  • 10+2 Intermediate Exam with 50% Marks and B.LEd 4 Year Course OR
  • 10+2 Inter Exam with 50% Marks and B.SC Ed Exam Passed

Age limit criteria:

The interested candidates must have fallen in the age limit criteria provided by the Uttar Pradesh Basic Education Board is:

  • For age relaxation criteria, you can refer to the notification. The link is given below in The ProGrad jobs.

Pay Scale:

  • The pay scale as per 7th pay commission for the post of Classes I-V (Primary Level), Classes VI-VIII (Upper Primary Level) is as per norms

How to apply for UP TET Online Form 2021?

  • First, visit the official website.
  • Register yourself on the portal of Uttar Pradesh Basic Education Board.
  • Login yourself on the portal.
  • Find the notification of Classes I-V (Primary Level), Classes VI-VIII (Upper Primary Level).
  • Fill up the complete details that are asked in the application form.
  • Upload your photo and signature with the dimensions asked in the instructions.
  • Submit the application fee
  • Finally, download the application form for future needs.
